narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would recommend this class. It's small, so very intimate and the professor is really nice and approachable. The class itself involves a fair amount of reading out loud in class but not a lot of acting. The workload is manageable; you get to practice your written German with frequent writing assignments and since the class is pretty small, you will be practicing your oral skills as well.
I would say take the class because it is required for the major. You read one play every 1-2 weeks and watch a few films of the plays. Interesting material.
A bit frustrating if you're looking for a seminar-like environment, but fine if you want to practice your German.
Yes, it is an interesting introduction to the historical interactions between politics/ theater in Germany.
